node.title: Slicing through the Canyon
node.description: Johnston creek in Banff carves a sharp path through the Canyon, sometimes giving the effect that large boulders will float away from the shore.

node.title: Peaks on Fire
node.description: My wife and I woke up extremely early one morning to catch the sunrise at Moraine Lake.  While we didnt get any clouds we were treated to some spectacular color on the mountains.  You might also notice what appears to be a small boat in the middle of the lake.  We found out later that a couple had paddled out on the lake during sunrise.  About the time I took this shot she was saying "Yes."

node.title: Secret Stream
node.description: One of the hidden streams in the forest along the Moraine Lake lake trail.  This was some COLD water!

node.title: It Is Well
node.description: Sunrise from Moraine Lake taken at lake level.  It was a serious scramble down the rocks to get this shot.  I really liked the way the foreground rock mirrored the shape of the reflected mountains.

node.title: Seat with a View
node.description: Sunrise from the Moraine Lake rock pile, looking out over Banff National Park.

node.title: Beautiful Finish
node.description: End of a beautiful sunset near Lake Louise, Alberta.

node.title: Sunset at the Ten Peaks
node.description: Sunset at Moraine Lake, Valley of the Ten Peaks.

node.title: Lake Louise Zen
node.description: Lake Louise after the storm.  Please view this one on black by pressing "L."

node.title: Wetlands Lily
node.description: Another shot from my outing with Brody J at the Bon Secour Refuge.  The reflection underneath the lily really caught my eye here.
